"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748697","Home Office","false","2017-07-12","<p>The Government’s policy paper (Cm 9464), which was laid before Parliament on 26 June, sets out our proposals that European Union (EU) citizens who arrive in the UK before the specified date and have five years’ continuous residence in the UK will be able to apply for UK settled status.</p><p> </p><p>The details of the settled status scheme will be subject to negotiations. We will publish further detail on the specifics of the new application process for settled status, including detailed eligibility criteria and requirements, in due course.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-07-12T09:56:35.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748697/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748697/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748697/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-07-05","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the policy paper, Safeguarding the position of EU citizens living in the UK and UK nationals living in the EU, published on 26 June 2017, whether the streamlined digital application process referred to in paragraph 35, page 12 will be available to EU citizens who do not have a passport.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","3007"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748698","Department for Education","false","2017-07-27","<p>The Government wants to create a world-beating technical education system and is investing heavily to ensure that it delivers the skills that the economy needs.</p><p> </p><p>We will deliver 3 million apprenticeships by 2020, and drive up the quality of apprenticeships to ensure they deliver the skills employers need.</p><p> </p><p>We are developing a system of technical education based on 15 new technical routes and introducing new qualifications, known as T-levels, which will provide clear pathways to jobs.</p><p> </p><p>We are also strengthening the provider base, including by establishing a network of new Institutes of Technology specialising in delivering higher-level technical skills.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-07-27T17:39:16.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748698/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748698/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748698/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-05","Skilled Workers: Vacancies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 26 June 2017 to Question 233, what steps are being taken to ensure that ongoing skills gaps of all types are filled.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","3006"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748699","Department of Health","false","2017-07-13","<p>NHS England is leading a review of medicines which may be considered as being of low clinical value and is working with NHS Clinical Commissioners to develop new guidance for clinical commissioning groups. NHS England expects to publish a consultation on the draft guidance shortly. The Department has not made an impact assessment on this work.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","3003 ; 3005 ; 3008","2017-07-13T12:59:07.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748699/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748699/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748699/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-07-05","Prescriptions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the projected savings are for the NHS of ending prescriptions for certain items that can be purchased over the counter.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","3004"
