"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748716","Department for Transport","false","2017-07-12","<p>The Department for Transport (DfT) is in discussions with Nexus regarding their proposals for new rolling stock on the Metro. DfT and HM Treasury officials continue to work with Nexus to explore various funding options.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-07-12T11:22:15.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748716/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748716/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748716/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-07-05","Tyne and Wear Metro: Rolling Stock","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what funding model his Department has proposed for the delivery of a new train fleet for the Tyne and Wear Metro.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","3049"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748717","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-12","<p>The Department works closely with the UK automotive industry, including through the Automotive Council, to understand the issues and opportunities the sector faces. The Government will continue its longstanding programme of support for the sector’s competitiveness. The UK has been very successful in attracting inward investment from automotive companies. Companies such as Nissan and Toyota have continued to re-invest, thanks to our highly-skilled workforce, strong partnership between government and industry, and long-term investment in new technology and innovation.</p><p>We are determined to ensure that the UK continues to be one of the most competitive locations in the world for automotive and advanced manufacturing. This includes seeking a tariff and barrier-free comprehensive free trade deal in goods and services with the EU for a new, mutually beneficial customs agreement that allows cross-border trade to be as frictionless as possible.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","3051","2017-07-12T09:41:42.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748717/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748717/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748717/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-05","Motor Vehicles: Manufacturing Industries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what contingency plans the Government has in place to offset the decline in investment in the automotive sector since 2015.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","3050"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748718","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-12","<p>The Department works closely with the UK automotive industry, including through the Automotive Council, to understand the issues and opportunities the sector faces. The Government will continue its longstanding programme of support for the sector’s competitiveness. The UK has been very successful in attracting inward investment from automotive companies. Companies such as Nissan and Toyota have continued to re-invest, thanks to our highly-skilled workforce, strong partnership between government and industry, and long-term investment in new technology and innovation.</p><p>We are determined to ensure that the UK continues to be one of the most competitive locations in the world for automotive and advanced manufacturing. This includes seeking a tariff and barrier-free comprehensive free trade deal in goods and services with the EU for a new, mutually beneficial customs agreement that allows cross-border trade to be as frictionless as possible.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","3050","2017-07-12T09:41:42.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748718/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748718/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748718/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-05","Motor Vehicles: Manufacturing Industries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps he is taking to encourage investment in the automotive industry.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","3051"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748720","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-11","<p>The Department does not separately identify the cost of sanctioning and monitoring claimants by benefit type.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-07-11T09:32:14.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748720/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748720/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748720/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-05","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much his Department has spent (a) sanctioning and (b) monitoring Employment and Support Allowance claimants over the last six months.","false","Biography information for Angela Crawley","Lanark and Hamilton East","Angela Crawley","3252"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748721","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-11","<p>There will be no cash losers among those who are already in receipt of Employment and Support Allowance (ESA) and we have laid regulations to protect existing ESA claimants, including those who temporarily leave the benefit to try out work and then return to ESA.</p><p> </p><p>The Government published its assessment of the impacts of the change to the work-related activity component on 20 July 2015. <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/documents/impact-assessments/IA15-006B.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/documents/impact-assessments/IA15-006B.pdf</a></p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-07-11T09:26:55.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748721/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748721/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748721/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-05","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of the abolition of the Employment and Support Allowance Work-Related Activity component on the incidence of claimant poverty.","false","Biography information for Angela Crawley","Lanark and Hamilton East","Angela Crawley","3253"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748722","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-11","<p>The information requested is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-07-11T09:38:27.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748722/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748722/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748722/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-05","Employment and Support Allowance: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people applying for Employment and Support Allowance in Scotland had to wait more than six weeks to receive their benefit in the last six months.","false","Biography information for Angela Crawley","Lanark and Hamilton East","Angela Crawley","3254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748723","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-07-10","<p>There is no condition based entitlement to Employment Support Allowance.</p><p> </p><p>We are working with medical professionals and other stakeholders to develop functional criteria that will help us identify those with the most severe health conditions or disabilities, for whom repeat work capability assessments can be stopped.</p><p> </p><p>Rather than a list of specific medical conditions, the criteria will be based on identifying claimants with the most severe health conditions or disabilities where it would be unreasonable to expect the individual to undertake any form or amount of work or work-related activity. This change will only apply to those placed in the Support Group and UC equivalent.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","3028","2017-07-10T10:20:23.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748723/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748723/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748723/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-07-05","Employment and Support Allowance: Motor Neurone Disease","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether claimants of employment and support allowance with motor neurone disease will continue to be subject to health reassessments.","false","Biography information for Sir Charles Walker","Broxbourne","Mr Charles Walker","3077"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748724","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-10","<p>DCLG publishes regular statistics on rough sleeping, statutory homelessness and homelessness prevention and relief. These are published at a local authority level. The latest statistics can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/homelessness-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/homelessness-statistics</a>.</p><p>The Government remains committed to combating homelessness and rough sleeping. No one should ever have to sleep rough. That is why we are aiming to halve rough sleeping by 2022 and eliminate it altogether by 2027. To achieve this, we will set up a new Homelessness Reduction Taskforce that will focus on prevention and affordable housing, and we will pilot a Housing First approach to tackle rough sleeping.</p><p>We also supported the Homelessness Reduction Act which received Royal Assent on 27 April 2017. The Act significantly reforms England’s homelessness legislation, ensuring that more people get the help they need earlier to prevent them from becoming homeless in the first place.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-07-10T16:40:44.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748724/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748724/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748724/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-07-05","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of the number of homeless people in (a) Coventry, (b) the West Midlands and (c) the UK.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","3038"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748725","Department for Education","false","2017-07-14","<p>The Government will continue to work to ensure that every child has the opportunity to attend a good school and that all schools are fairly funded. The core schools budget has been protected in real terms since 2010 and is set to rise from £41 billion in 2017-18 to over £42 billion in 2019-20 with increasing pupil numbers.</p><p> </p><p>We received over 25,000 responses to the consultation. We are grateful to all those who expressed their views on school funding and the proposed formula as part of this process. We will publish the response to the consultation in due course.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-07-14T12:39:25.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748725/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748725/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748725/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-05","Schools: Coventry South","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment her Department has made of the effect of the new school funding formula for each school in Coventry South constituency.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","3137"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748726","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-13","<p>The Government’s National Cyber Security Strategy (2016-2021, https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-cyber-security-strategy-2016-to-2021) sets out a five-year transformational plan, backed with £1.9 billion investment, to make Britain secure and resilient in cyberspace. This includes opening the National Cyber Security Centre (NCSC) to help make the UK the safest place to live and do business online. The Cyber Essentials scheme sets out measures businesses should take to protect themselves from the most common internet threats and the Cyber Aware campaign offers simple and practical advice to help small businesses stay safe online. A wide range of regularly updated cyber security guidance and support is available via the NCSC website www.ncsc.gov.uk and on www.gov.uk. My Department is also funding the development of two Cyber Innovation Centres in London and Cheltenham to help ensure businesses have access to cutting edge technology to help maintain their cyber security.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-07-13T14:54:46.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748726/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748726/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748726/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-05","Cybercrime: Business","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what (a) financial and (b) other steps she is taking to help protect businesses from future cyber threats; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","3106"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748727","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-07-10","<p>We are committed to ensuring, by the best means possible, that a system of uninterrupted data flows between EU Member States and the UK can continue after we leave the EU.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-07-10T13:10:06.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748727/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748727/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748727/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-07-05","Data Protection: EU Law","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, whether her Department has made an estimate of how long it will take for the UK to agree an adequacy agreement to share data with EU countries once the UK leaves the EU; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","3133"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748728","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-10","<p>The Government is committed to ensuring that every home and small business in the country is offered a smart meter the end of 2020. The Programme is making good progress and consumers are already benefiting from smart meters. There are now almost 7 million meters operating across homes and business in Great Britain: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/statistical-release-and-data-smart-meters-great-britain-quarter-1-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/statistical-release-and-data-smart-meters-great-britain-quarter-1-2017</a></p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-10T16:16:32.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748728/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748728/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748728/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-05","Energy: Meters","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of whether the smart meter roll-out is proceeding according to timetable; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","3134"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748729","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-07-10","<p>Centrica Storage Ltd’s decision to close the Rough gas storage facility is a commercial decision based on the age of the asset and the costs of repair. As such, we do not have the information to undertake a comprehensive assessment of the effect on wholesale gas prices of maintaining the gas storage facility at Rough. However, Rough was unavailable in the market last winter, and we believe this was largely expected by market participants so we don’t expect any significant effect on prices.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2017-07-10T16:49:53.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748729/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748729/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748729/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-07-05","Natural Gas: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the effect on the closure of the Rough gas storage facility on domestic gas prices; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","3043"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748730","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-10","<p>Ministry of Defence officials have regular discussions with their Australian colleagues on many aspects of military capability and equipment collaboration, including the capabilities of our respective shipbuilding industries.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-07-10T14:21:38.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748730/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748730/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748730/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-05","Warships: Shipbuilding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the UK-Australia Defence Co-operation Treaty and Australia-UK MOU on Military Capability Harmonisation and Equipment Cooperation (AUMICE), what representations his Department has made to the Australian Government on the UK's shipbuilding industry's capabilities.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748731","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-10","<p>The training of the Libyan Navy Coastguard in basic seamanship skills makes up a small proportion of the Op SOPHIA Activity. The UK specifically have trained 18 Libyan Navy Coastguard. This took place between 16 October to 28 November 2016.</p><p>The overall net additional cost was £35,000.</p><p>More Libyan Naval Coastguard training is planned for later in 2017.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","3208","2017-07-10T16:41:16.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748731/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748731/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748731/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-05","Mediterranean Sea: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Libyan Coastguard personnel have participated in training provided by armed forces personnel as part of the UK's support to Operation Sophia in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3207"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748732","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-10","<p>The training of the Libyan Navy Coastguard in basic seamanship skills makes up a small proportion of the Op SOPHIA Activity. The UK specifically have trained 18 Libyan Navy Coastguard. This took place between 16 October to 28 November 2016.</p><p>The overall net additional cost was £35,000.</p><p>More Libyan Naval Coastguard training is planned for later in 2017.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","3207","2017-07-10T16:41:16.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748732/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748732/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748732/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-05","Mediterranean Sea: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will estimate the cost of training Libyan Coastguard personnel as part of the UK's support to Operation Sophia.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3208"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748733","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-10","<p>My Ministerial colleagues and I hold regular and frequent discussions with our Australian counterparts. Amongst other matters, we have discussed a variety of capability co-operation subjects, including the Royal Australian Navy's Future Frigate requirement.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-07-10T14:20:47.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748733/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748733/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748733/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-05","Australia: Navy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent discussions he has had with his Australian counterpart on the Royal Australian Navy Future Frigate requirement.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3209"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748734","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-11","<p>Under the current Royal Navy/Royal Australian Navy personnel exchange programme, 12 Royal Navy Officers are attached to the British High Commission in Canberra. These Officers are based in different Australian Navy ships and shore establishments. 11 Australian personnel are on exchange tours with the Naval Service.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","3177","2017-07-11T15:10:26.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748734/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748734/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748734/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-05","Navy: Officers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Royal Navy officers are attached to the British High Commission in Canberra.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3176"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748735","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-07-11","<p>Under the current Royal Navy/Royal Australian Navy personnel exchange programme, 12 Royal Navy Officers are attached to the British High Commission in Canberra. These Officers are based in different Australian Navy ships and shore establishments. 11 Australian personnel are on exchange tours with the Naval Service.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","3176","2017-07-11T15:10:26.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748735/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748735/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/748735/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-05","Australia: Navy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Royal Australian Navy personnel are on exchange tours with the Royal Navy.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3177"
